{"id":1243,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":1243,"title":"Watches","subtitle":"","short_title":"Watches","uri":"/scriptures/bd/watches","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/watches.t1","order":".000.3974"},[".title","Watches"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/watches.p1","order":".000.3975"},"The Jews, like the Babylonians and Greeks, divided the night into three watches, “the beginning of the watches,” sunset till 10",["span.smallCaps","p.m."],"(",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/lam/2.19"},"Lam. 2:19"],"); the “middle watch,” 10",["span.smallCaps","p.m."],"till 2",["span.smallCaps","a.m."],"(",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/7.19"},"Judg. 7:19"],"); and the “morning watch,” 2",["span.smallCaps","a.m."],"till sunrise (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/14.24"},"Ex. 14:24"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/11.11"},"1 Sam. 11:11"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/12.38"},"Luke 12:38"],"). The Romans had four watches, and it is their practice that is followed in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/14.25"},"Matt. 14:25"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/6.48"},"Mark 6:48"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/13.35"},"13:35"],"."]]],"refs":null}
